quran[4]{c,v,t}:
  106,1,The privilege of protection enjoyed by the Qureysh
  106,2,"safe passage of their trading caravans in the winter and the summer (due to their being the caretakers of the House of Allah, and they know this fact)"
  106,3,So they should worship the Lord of this House
  106,4,Who provided them food in the days of famine and made them secure against fear